# SmartDay — environment variables template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your real values.
# .env.local is git-ignored — NEVER commit real credentials.
#
# How to get these values:
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#   2. Create a project (or select an existing one)
#   3. Enable "Google Calendar API"
#   4. Create credentials:
#        - OAuth 2.0 Client ID  → paste below as VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
#        - API Key               → paste below as VITE_GOOGLE_API_KEY
#   5. In "Authorised JavaScript origins" add: http://localhost:5173
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here.apps.googleusercontent.com
VITE_GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
